term_inventory_greek.meaning:
God-loving God
God-loving, pious;
a lover of God, 2Tim. 3:4*

dearly loved one;
the object of special affection and of special relationship, as with Jesus the beloved of the Father
beloved, dear;
worthy of love

brother, fellow countryman, neighbor (often inclusive in gender);
by extension a fellow believer in the family of faith;
in the plural "brothers" regularly refers to men and women
a brother, near kinsman, or relative;
one of the same nation or nature;
one of equal rank and dignity;
an associate, a member of the Christian community

brotherly love;
brotherly kindness
brotherly love, brotherly kindness;
, in NT love of the Christian brotherhood, Rom. 12:10; 1Thess. 4:9; Heb. 13:1; 1Pet. 1:22; 2Pet. 1:7*

contentious, quarrelsome
fond of contention;
contentious, disputatious, quarrelsome 1Cor. 11:16*

husband-loving one’s husband
husband-loving;
conjugal, Tit. 2:4*

love, in the NT usually the active love of God for his Son and his people, and the active love his people are to have for God, each other, and even enemies;
love feast, the common meal shared by Christians in connection with church meetings
love, generosity, kindly concern, devotedness;
, plural love-feasts, Jude 12

dispute, strife
a love of contention;
rivalry, contention, dispute Lk. 22:24*

loving pleasure -loving
pleasure-loving;
a lover of pleasure, 2Tim. 3:4*

to love;
in the NT usually the active love of God for his Son and his people, and the active love his people are to have for God, each other, and even enemies
to love, value, esteem, feel or manifest generous concern for, be faithful towards;
to delight in, to set store upon, Rev. 12:11

to love, to have affection and regard of a very high order, not unlike G0026, and overlapping in meaning in some contexts
primarily to manifest some act or token of kindness or affection;
to kiss, Mt. 26:48; Mk. 14:44; Lk. 22:47;
to love, regard with affection, have affection for, Mt. 10:37; Jn. 5:20;
to like, be fond of, delight in a thing, Mt. 23:6; Rev. 22:15; to cherish inordinately, set store by, Jn. 12:25
